http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/%E2%80%98Aranmula-typifies-communal-harmony%E2%80%99/article14000325.ece

The Aranmula Uthrittathi snakeboat regatta (Vallamkali), the annual festival at the Sree Parthasarathy temple, and the century-old Maramon convention symbolised the region’s communal harmony, the Mar Thoma Metropolitan, Joseph Mar Thoma, has said.The supreme head of the Mar Thoma Syrian Church of Malabar was inaugurating the public reception accorded to the new State president of the Bharatiya Janata Party, Kummanam Rajasekharan, at Aranmula on Friday.He said Aranmula was Kerala’s symbol of religious tolerance. Lauding Mr. Rajasekharan’s leadership quality, the Metropolitan said the former, in his new capacity as the BJP State chief, would be able to sustain the religious tolerance in the State.Philipose Mar Chrysostum, Metropolitan emeritus of the Mar Thoma Church, and Akkeeramon Kalidasa Bhattathirippad, Kerala Yogakshema Sabha former president, delivered the benedictory speeches.The reception was organised by the Aranmula Pouravali (citizens’ forum), comprising people of different parties, environmentalists, and socio-religious workers. Hindumatha Maha Mandalam president T.N. Upendranatha Kurup presided over the public function held at the Iykara junction.Thomas P. Thomas, reception committee chairman; Mathew Koshy Punnackad, director of the Ecological Concerns Department of the Church of South India; Jose Parakkadavil, District Kathakali Club president; N.K. Sukumaran Nair, Pampa Parirakshana Samiti general secretary; K.G. Sasidharan Pillai, Palliyoda Seva Sanghom president were among those who spoke.